        "text": "### What Was Confirmed\n\n| Entity | SRD-46 ID | Key Stats |\n|--------|-----------|-----------|\n| Cadmium(II) | metal_26 | 818 ligands · 2,828 VLMs · 95 β-definitions |\n\nThe Cd²⁺ entry is data-rich, but **chloride did not appear in the top-10 ligands by VLM count** for Cd²⁺. Searches by name (\"chloride\", \"chloro\"), SMILES (`[Cl-]`), and formula did not return the simple halide anion as a discrete ligand. This is a known quirk of some thermodynamic databases where simple halides are stored under non-obvious names (e.g., \"Cl⁻\", \"chloro ion\", or embedded in ionic-medium descriptions).",
