        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "### Chemistry Context (from established literature, not SRD-46 retrieval)\n\nThe Cd²⁺–Cl⁻ system is one of the most extensively studied halide systems. For reference, the broader literature reports:\n\n| Species | Typical log β (25 °C, I → 0) | Stoichiometry |\n|---------|-------------------------------|---------------|\n| CdCl⁺ | ~1.95–2.00 | ML |\n| CdCl₂⁰ | ~2.60–2.70 | ML₂ |\n| CdCl₃⁻ | ~2.40–2.50 | ML₃ |\n| CdCl₄²⁻ | ~1.70–2.00 | ML₄ |\n\nConditions reported in the literature span **ionic strengths of 0–5 mol/L** (NaClO₄ or NaCl media) and **temperatures of 15–45 °C**. NIST SRD-46 historically compiles on the order of **20–40 independent sources** for this system.",
